openapi: 3.0.0
info:
  title: Low Value and ACH Payments API
  description: Initiate low-value ACH credit transfers across the globe with this API, giving you detailed control over payment instructions and account details, while receiving real-time status updates through secure, digitally signed requests. You can easily support multiple payment schemes in WHEM (Western Hemisphere;  North, Central, and South America), EMEA (Europe, Middle East, and Africa), and APAC (Asia-Pacific) regions, streamlining your payment operations and tracking every transaction as it happens.
  version: 1.1.1
servers:
  - url: https://apigateway.jpmorgan.com/tsapi/v1
    description: PRODUCTION - MTLS
  - url: https://apigatewayqaf.jpmorgan.com/tsapi/v1
    description: CLIENT TESTING - MTLS

tags:
  - name: Payment Initiation
    description: description
paths:
  /payments/ach/credit:
    post:
      summary: Payment Initiation
      operationId: initiateCreditTransfer
      description: "\n### DIGITAL SIGNATURE REQUIRED ###\n\n\n To view detailed data mapping for API request fields, including field descriptions and requirements by payment type and geography, [sign in to your account](https://developer.payments.jpmorgan.com/console/login) and add the product to your Personal Workspace. This provides access to the full spreadsheet, which outlines each field and indicates whether it is required, optional, or conditionally required for your use case, as well as other downloadable reference materials available in the workspace. For instructions, refer to our [Quick Start Guide](https://payments-developer-portal.prod.aws.jpmchase.net/preview/docs/quick-start).\n\n- The endToEndId field must not exceed 15-characters.\n- Only alphanumeric characters are allowed in endToEndId. Any non-alphanumeric values may cause processing issues. Hyphens and colons are not permitted as the first character.\n- If alphabetic characters are used in endToEndId, they must be uppercase. \n- The retention period for endToEndId can be six months or one year, depending on your production setup. Reusing the same endToEndId within the retention period will result in payment rejection. After the retention period, the same endToEndId can be reused.\n- The Payment Status Track and Trace API can be queried using endToEndId. If more than one payment exists with the same endToEndId after the retention period, the API will return the status of the latest payment.\n- The Content-Type header must be set to text/xml, with the payload being a digitally signed version of the JSON request body as documented in this specification.\n"
      parameters: []
      x-examples:
        - name: USD ACH Credit Transfer (Mandatory Fields)
          description: USD ACH Credit Transfer (Mandatory Fields)
          parameters:
            ClientDN: CN=apigatewaydev.jpmchase.net, OU=TSS, O=JPMorgan Chase, L=New York, ST=New York, C=US
